{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KqXm2yanumbWs4aNvyBonc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/feedback.md`.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe single failure traces to **two interacting bugs** in the trilingual title layout (`Smażona zielona fasolka` / `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` / `그린빈 볶음`):\n\n**Primary cause — bilingual join contamination:** The bilingual detection correctly removes `\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` as a standalone candidate, but the filter only suppresses candidates *starting with* the translation text. The 2-line join `\"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` and 3-line join including Korean both pass `passesHardFilters` and remain in `scoredForThreshold`. These composite candidates have blended Polish+English embeddings that likely outscore the clean Polish-only title (English food terms like \"GREEN BEANS\" are strongly recognized by the embedding model).\n\n**Secondary cause — structural bonus misallocation:** `\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"` qualifies as `firstStructuralHeading` (ALL_CAPS, 3 words, all ≥4 chars) before bilingual detection runs. It gets `structuralBonus=0.10` + `allCapsBonus=0.08` baked into `scored`. The actual title `\"Smażona zielona fasolka\"` gets zero bonuses. Even after the standalone translation is suppressed, its score dominates the fallback path.\n\n**Fix direction:** Extend bilingual suppression to also remove candidates that *contain* translation text as a contiguous substring (not just as a leading prefix), and avoid assigning structural bonuses to candidates that are subsequently identified as translations."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3797,"cache_read_input_tokens":60247,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3797},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},